info.title: Cloudhub
info.description: A comprehensive set of RESTful services, allowing you to seamlessly integrate with Trimble Transportation Management Systems (TruckMate, Suite, and ICC) in a unified way.

tags.name: Accessorial Charge Codes
tags.description: The Accessorial Charge Codes endpoints within CloudHub allows for retrieving Transportation Management System (TMS) specific accessorial charge code records. The records are pulled directly from each TMS.

tags.name: Commodities
tags.description: The Commodities endpoints within CloudHub allows for retrieving Transportation Management System (TMS) specific commodity records. The records are pulled directly from each TMS.

tags.name: Documents
tags.description: The Documents endpoints within CloudHub allows for public viewing of specific imaging documents through a URL linked with a time sensitive token.

tags.name: Drivers

tags.name: Position Events

tags.name: Quotes
tags.description: The Quotes endpoint within CloudHub allows for requesting a new quote directly from the Transportation Management System (TMS). Historical quotes can also be retrieved from each TMS. Existing quotes can be converted into a new tender or freight order.

tags.name: Service Levels

get.summary: Retrieve a document from the image system
get.description:
Retrieves a document from the imaging server.
The document type and document identifier path parameters are used along with the token provided in the query string to determine access to the document.
Documents will be converted and returned in the specified document format (only PDF is supported at this time).

parameters.name: documentFormat
parameters.description: Format in which to return document (only PDF is supported currently)

post.description:
Generates a time sensitive token to be used in subsequent calls to retrieve the specific document from the imaging system.
The document type, as configured in the imaging system, and a document identifier are required path parameters.

requestBody.description: A single JSON object containing the length of time the token should be valid. Default expiry is one week, if no payload is provided.

get.description: Retrieves a driver's availability record from the TMS.

Retrieves freight order records from the TMS. Freight orders are a collection of freight items that are moved from one or more locations to one or more other locations using a common freight equipment type, hauling mode, carrier, and transit service level. An empty load moves equipment only without any freight.

get.description:
Retrieves status history records for the specified trip.

 Use the $filter parameter to apply an oData filter on the status property to exclude POSITION updates.

 For example:

* $filter=status ne POSITION

 Trip status history can be viewed on the Trip Envelope Processing application > shortcut menu > Trip Status History window.

pageSize.name: pageSize
pageSize.description: Specifies the maximum number of items to include in the response results.

pageIndex.name: pageIndex
pageIndex.description: Specifies the number of items to skip before beginning to select the records to return.

filter.name: $filter
filter.description: Filter items by property values, see [Filtering](http://docs.oasis-open.org/odata/odata/v4.01/odata-v4.01-part1-protocol.html#sec_SystemQueryOptionfilter). Note, not all features of oData filter syntax are supported.

sortBy.name: sortBy
sortBy.description: Field(s) to sort returned resource by, with optional direction. E.g., "fieldName desc, fieldName2"

select.name: $select
select.description: Select allows to request a specific set of properties, see [Selecting](http://docs.oasis-open.org/odata/odata/v4.01/odata-v4.01-part2-url-conventions.html#_Toc31361040)

codeBehavior.name: codeBehavior
codeBehavior.description: Filter trips by status code behavior. Can be used with a single value (e.g. codeBehavior=dispatch) or combined with an IN or NOT IN operator (e.g. codeBehavior=NOT IN (complete, cancel).

loadOfferOnly.name: loadOfferOnly
loadOfferOnly.description: Filter trips by load offer only. If set to true, only trips with load offers will be returned.

sourceCode.description: Application where a record originated and source ids are recognized, eg TM, TMWS, ICC

sourceReferenceId.description: Identifier of a database instance where a record originated

sourceId.description: A unique system-generated identifier of an object where it originated

expiresIn.description: Optional. Time in seconds after which this token should expire.

id.description: Internal unique identifier for the document token.

token.description: Random alphanumeric string that can be used to securely access a document without additional authentication.

expiresAt.description: Date after which the token will no longer be valid for document access.
